ဒပ်ပၞာန်ဝဂှ် ကောန်ပၞာန် နွံ ၃၀,၀၀၀ တုဲ ကောန်ဒပ်အရန် နွံ ၁၀,၀၀၀။<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www2.irrawaddy.org/article.php?art_id=22013 |title=Irrawaddy |access-date=29 November 2014}}</ref> ပၞောဝ်ကဵု ဒပ်မဒေါအ်လဝ် ပန်ပှ်ော ကုအလဵုအသဳဗၟာမ္ဂး ဒှ်ဒပ် ဒြဟတ်ဇၞော်အိုတ်တုဲ ကောန်ပၞာန်မွဲမ္ဂး ကလိဂွံ သြန်ဂိတု မွဲဂိတု လှုဲကြုက် ၆၀ ယာန် (US$7.5)ဓဝ်ရ။<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.english.panglong.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4898:united-wa-state-army-uwsa-payroll-still-going-communist-way&catid=93:general&Itemid=291 |title=United Wa State Army (UWSA) payroll still going Communist way |author=S.H.A.N. |access-date=29 November 2014}}</ref> ဒပ်ပၞာန်ဝ ဒှ်ပေါဲဗတိုက် ကုဒပ်ပၞာန်ဍုင်သေံ ပ္ဍဲဂိတုမာတ်-မေ ၂၀၀၂။<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.nationmultimedia.com/opinion/Talk-of-reopened-border-stirs-bad-memories-for-arm-30189119.html |title = Talk of reopened border stirs bad memories for army |date=27 August 2012 |work = The Nation |access-date=29 November 2014}}</ref>

=== လွဟ် ===
အတိုင် ''[[Jane's Intelligence Review]]'' မပ္တိတ်လဝ် ပ္ဍဲဂိတုဨပြဳ ၂၀၀၈ မ္ဂး ဍုင်ကြုက်ဂှ် ဒှ်ဒၞာဲ ပၞာန်ဝ မကလိဂွံ လွဟ်အဓိကတုဲ နူကဵု ဗွဝ်ဖျာကမၠတ် ပ္ဍဲအာရှအဂၞဲဂှ်လေဝ် ညးတအ် ကလိဂွံလွဟ်နွံကီုရ။<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.indianexpress.com/story/312894.html |author = Pubby, Manu|title = China emerging as main source of arms to N-E rebels: Jane's Review |work = Indianexpress|access-date= 8 June 2008}}</ref> A ''Jane'''s report in December 2008 stated that the UWSA had turned to arms production to supplement their income from arms and drug trafficking, and started a [[small arms]] production line for [[AK 47]]s.<ref name="lw">{{cite magazine |url=http://www2.irrawaddy.org/article.php?art_id=14804 |author=Lawi Weng |title=AK-47s – Made in Wa State|magazine=[[The Irrawaddy]] |date= 16 December 2008 |access-date=22 December 2008}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url = http://www2.irrawaddy.org/article.php?art_id=14829|author=Lawi Weng |title = Armed Insurgents in Burma Face Shortage of Ammunition |publisher=[[The Irrawaddy]] 22 December 2008 |access-date = 22 December 2008}}</ref>

Jane's reported in 2001 that the UWSA had acquired [[HN-5]]N [[Surface-to-air missile]] (SAMs) from China as part of the build-up near the Thai border where they were reported to be operating 40–50 laboratories manufacturing ''[[Methamphetamine|yaa baa]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.janes.com/security/international_security/news/jdw/jdw010328_2_n.shtml |first= Anthony |last= Davis |title=Myanmar heat turned up with SAMs from China |publisher=[[Jane's Information Group]]|date=28 March 2001|access-date=5 March 2009}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> In November 2014, Janes further reported that the UWSA have acquired the [[FN-6]] [[Surface-to-air missile]] to supplant the [[HN-5]]N in service,<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.janes.com/article/45910/uwsa-fielding-chinese-fn-6-manpads |first= Anthony|last= Davis |title=UWSA fielding Chinese FN-6 MANPADS |publisher=[[Jane's Information Group]]|date=18 November 2014|access-date=23 November 2014}}</ref> which was promptly denied by the UWSA.<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.irrawaddy.org/burma/united-wa-state-army-denies-anti-aircraft-purchase.html |title=United Wa State Army Denies Anti-Aircraft Purchase |publisher=[[The Irrawaday]] |date=20 November 2014 |access-date=23 November 2014}}</ref> It is also the middleman between Chinese arms manufacturers and other insurgent groups in Myanmar.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://asiancorrespondent.com/93164/can-burma-influence-wa-army-to-abide-by-its-constitution/ |title=Asian Correspondent |access-date=29 November 2014}}</ref> By 2012, Chinese support had increased to the point of supplying armoured vehicles such as the 6&nbsp;×&nbsp;6 PTL-02 assault gun being sighted in [[Pangkham]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/library/news/2013/01/mil-130125-voa05.htm |title=With Burma in Mind, China Quietly Supports Wa Rebels. |author=John Pike |access-date=29 November 2014}}</ref>

On 29 April 2013, Janes IHS reported that several [[Mil Mi-17]] helicopters armed with TY-90 air-to-air missiles were supplied to UWSA by China.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20140425180018/www.janes.com/article/12159/china-sends-armed-helicopters-to-myanmar-separatists</ref> The allegations were dismissed by China, [[Royal Thai Armed Forces|Thai military]] sources, other Myanmar ethnic sources and the UWSA themselves.<ref>{{cite news |title = After Chinese Arms Allegations, UWSA Shows Off 'Thai' Military Hardware |url = http://www.irrawaddy.org/archives/34538|access-date=14 May 2013 |newspaper=The Irrawaddy|date=14 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title = Doubts cast on Wa helicopter rumors |url = http://www.mizzima.com/news/ethnic-issues/9562-doubts-cast-on-wa-helicopter-rumors |access-date = 20 June 2013 |newspaper = Mizzima News |date = 20 June 2013 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130620101019/http://mizzima.com/news/ethnic-issues/9562-doubts-cast-on-wa-helicopter-rumors |archive-date = 20 June 2013 |url-status = dead }}</ref> In 2015 IHS Jane's reported that UWSA members had been photographed training with Chinese Type 96 122&nbsp;mm howitzers and HJ-8 ATGMs.<ref name="JanesDefence" />

== Territory ==
The towns of [[Pangkham]] and [[Mong Pawk]] are within the area of this special region.<ref name="pac" /> The UWSA negotiated a [[cease-fire]] agreement with the [[Tatmadaw|Burmese military]] in the 1990s, and currently backs a [[counterinsurgency]] strategy of the [[Tatmadaw|Myanmar Army]] against the [[Shan State Army-South]] (SSA-S).<ref name="lw" /> The UWSA defied the [[State Peace and Development Council|military regime]]'s recent demand to disarm and participate in the 2010 [[elections]], and instead proposed to declare the territory under their control as a special [[autonomous]] region.<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www2.irrawaddy.org/highlight.php?art_id=14874 |author=Lawi Weng |title = UWSP Proposes Wa Autonomous Region |publisher=[[The Irrawaddy]] magazine, 5 January 2009 |access-date=5 January 2009}}</ref>

According to 2008 constitution, six townships are designated as the [[Wa Self-Administered Division]]. Those are [[Mongmao]], [[Pangwaun Township|Pangwaun]], [[Namphan Township|Namphan]], [[Pangkham]] (Pangsang), [[Hopang]] and [[Matman Township]]. Although [[Mong Pawk]] is not part of it, but part of [[Mong Yang Township]], the UWSA was strongly against to give away that area from its control because it serves as a link with its ally, the [[National Democratic Alliance Army]] (NDAA) in [[Mong La Township|Mongla]]. Hopang and Matman are not under UWSA control.<ref name="english.panglong.org"/> UWSA announced its territory as Wa State Government Special Administrative Region in January 2009.<ref>[http://www.mizzima.com/news/inside-burma/7521-powerful-wa-army-considers-becoming-peoples-militia-force.html Mizzima] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120713114655/http://www.mizzima.com/news/inside-burma/7521-powerful-wa-army-considers-becoming-peoples-militia-force.html |date=13 July 2012 }}</ref>


